The US changes the rules for obtaining a visa
The persons must present themselves before their interview with the consulate to the service agencies for visa applications; costs will be reduced in this way.
From 10 January 2011, the procedures for applying for a visa will change in the United States Embassy and in the Consulates.
The new procedure requires most applicants to present themselves to the visa application services (ASC, the initial letters in English) before their consultation at the consulate.
The staff of the ASC shall record the biometric data of the applicant, which shall be verified by the consulate before the interview.
The new procedure has certain advantages for the aspirants, including:
The total cost of handling the visa is reduced because it is no longer necessary to pay separately the time-limit agreement, the processing of the visa application and the transport service with which the document is issued.
The applicant shall make only one payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the equivalent of 140 dollars for a tourist visa, 150 dollars for visas with application (including visa for temporary workers) and 390 dollars for traders and investors.
Those who only want to extend their visa do not need to have a conversation at the consulate, they only have to imagine the next ASC where they will submit their documents and their fingerprints will be taken.
As the biometric data are collected in the ASC, the applicants who need a second date for the consulate will remain there for less time than before.
Those who apply for the visa in the consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo no longer have to pay the 26-dollar service premium.
Further information on the new visa application procedure can be found on the following website: http: / / mexico.usembassy.gov / boletines / sp101201 _ Visas-FAQs.html
